== Description == <!--T:3-->

<!--T:4-->
The {{Button|[[Image:Assembly_ConstraintSketchPlane.svg|24px]] [[Assembly3_ConstraintSketchPlane|Sketch plane]]}} command creates a "Sketch plane" as a container for Draft objects. 

<!--T:8-->
It can be used to create a skeleton sketch for 2D kinematics.

== Usage == <!--T:5--> 

<!--T:6-->
# Create an empty assembly container by pressing {{Button|[[Image:Assembly_New_Assembly.svg‎‎|16px]] [[Assembly3_CreateAssembly|Create assembly]]}}
# Select the newly created assembly object, and click {{Button|[[Image:Assembly_Add_Workplane.svg‎‎|16px]] [[Assembly3_AddWorkplane|Add workplane]]}}
# Press the {{Button|[[Image:Assembly_ConstraintSketchPlane.svg|24px]] [[Assembly3_ConstraintSketchPlane|Sketch plane]]}} button
# Switch to the [[Image:Workbench_Draft.svg|24px]] [[Draft_Workbench|Draft Workbench]] to add some content

<!--T:9-->
: With an existing non-empty assembly steps 1 and 2 can be skipped and any planar face element can be used as a work plane for the sketch plane.


